  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Obstacle
    interface for all obstacles in the game to follow.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Accel  
    Ball
    The bouncing ball.
    BumperObstacleLine
    This class creates a bumber obstacle for the game.
    ButtonObstacle
    Button obstacles for the game, a cirlce that prevents the ball from passing through it and grants points when hit.
    CollisionResponse
    This object captures the collision responses, if collision is detected.
    FormulaPanel
    The panel that contains physics formulas for the user to refer to.
    GameEngine
    The main class to run the gameplay.
    HighScore
    Data class to contain a highscore.
    HighScoreManager
    This is the main class for handling highscores.
    HighScorePanel
    Panel for displaying the highscores.
    InstructionsPanel
    Panel that displays the instructions of the game.
    MoveEngine
    This is the engine that calculates all collisions and movement in the game.
    ObstacleLine
    An obstacle line-Segment with two definite end-points.
    PausePanel
    The main panel for the paused screen.
    PauseWindow
    The window used to host the pause menu during the game.
    PseudoPaddle
    The paddle controlled by the user to prevent the ball from falling into the gutter
